</input></program>
            </TabNode></exercise>
        <p>Note that the high level language is much more compact than the assembly or machine code and, even more important, it allows us to express an algorithm at a level much closer to the actual problem domain. Instead of worrying about LOADing and STOREing values into registers, we can express commands that look more like normal calculations: <c>tip = mealCost * 0.15</c>.</p>
